The paper discusses the applications of unsupervised machine learning in networking, which involves the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning for traffic engineering, anomaly detection, Internet traffic classification, and quality of service optimization, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning for classification, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning for optimal control, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning for developing autonomous self-driving cars, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
